title: Death records Nicole Paetz (Mclennan County Health)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All Death records for Nicole Paetz, birthdate August, 21, 1962 
Died in Waco, Tx at local hospital on or around February 13, 2023

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Stacy Tarvin

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Produce all details and communications of the planned trip mentioned in this article:

 https://www.sfexaminer.com/news/politics/sf-leaders-to-tour-safe-drug-consumption-sites-in-nyc/article_c1dfca64-b3c3-11ed-9f8b-4f4cd9b51e09.html?utm_medium=social&utm_source=twitter_sfexaminer

INCLUDING:

Who is paying for the trips and expenses.

Who is going on the trip including the names, organizations, and titles of individuals mentioned here: 

“…several nonprofit leaders working to open a supervised consumption site in San Francisco are expected to go, as are representatives from the San Francisco Bar Association and the Public Defender’s Office.”

Please include:

Names of nonprofits; names of nonprofit leaders and anyone else from nonprofits attending.

Names and titles of “representatives from the San Francisco Bar Association and the Public Defender’s Office.”

Please also provide:

All details and costs of entire trip

Source of funding for entire trip


In all cases, produce exact copies of communications and search govt accounts/devices and also personal accounts/devices of every form or app.  Preserve all participants, email addresses, date/time stamps, to/from/cc/bcc, attachments (in their original electronic form).

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Belle Reve
